        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 3:11PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Skyline, or 12 miles northwest of Scottsboro, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stevenson, Hollywood, Skyline, Anderson, Pleasant Groves, Hytop,
Bass, Martintown, Princeton, and Jericho.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
